Key Points (Concepts Used):

This problem belongs to Fixed Size Sliding Window.
Window size is always k.
Instead of checking every substring again (O(n*k)), we reuse the previous window computation.
Steps followed:
Count vowels in the first window (0 → k-1).
Store this count.
Slide the window one step at a time.
When sliding:
Remove the left character.
Add the new right character.
Update the maximum vowel count.
This reduces complexity to:
Time Complexity: O(n)
Space Complexity: O(1)
Key sliding window idea:
Don't recompute the whole window
Only adjust the characters entering and leaving the window.

OPTIMZED CODE: TIME COMPLEXITY:O(N) || SPACE COMPLEXITY:O(1)
class Solution {
    public int maxVowels(String s, int k) {
        int max=Integer.MIN_VALUE,count=0;
        if(s.length()==1)
        {
            if(s.charAt(0)=='a' || s.charAt(0)=='e' || s.charAt(0)=='i' || s.charAt(0)=='o' || s.charAt(0)=='u')
            {
                return 1;
            }
        }
        for(int i=0;i<k;i++)
        {
            if(s.charAt(i)=='a' || s.charAt(i)=='e' || s.charAt(i)=='i' || s.charAt(i)=='o' || s.charAt(i)=='u')
                {
                    count++;
                }
        }
        int j=0;
        for(int i=k;i<s.length();i++)
        {
            char remove=s.charAt(j);
            char add=s.charAt(i);
            max=Math.max(count,max);
            if(remove=='a' || remove=='e' || remove=='i' ||remove=='o' ||remove=='u')
                {
                    count--;
                }
            if(add=='a' || add=='e' || add=='i' ||add=='o' || add=='u')
                {
                    count++;
                }
            j++;
        }
        max=Math.max(count,max);
        return max;
    }
}
